examples.en: 'I did no such thing,' he protested.
She protested that the law was unfair.
The coach protested the referee's call.
Students protested at the civil rights rally.
The decision was protested by dozens of people.
'That's not true,' she protested in a shrill voice.
They protested the inequitable treatment of employees.
The whole street protested the absence of street lights.
'That's not what I mean, and you know it,' he protested.
They protested the government's violation of human rights.
If it's protested against by all the people, the government can hardly refuse to take notice.
